{"title_page": "Behnam Taebi", "text_new": "{{short description|Dutch ethicist and academician|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Orphan|date=February 2019}}\n{{Infobox academic\n| honorific_prefix   = \n| name               = Behnam Taebi\n| honorific_suffix   = \n| image              = \n| image_size         = \n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| native_name        = \u0628\u0647\u0646\u0627\u0645 \u062a\u0627\u0626\u0628\u06cc\n| native_name_lang   = Persian\n| birth_name         = Behnam Taebi\n| birth_date         = \n| birth_place        = 1977\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| death_cause        = \n| region             = \n| nationality        = Dutch\n| citizenship        = Dutch\n| residence          = [[The Netherlands]]\n| other_names        = \n| occupation         = \n| period             = \n| known_for          = \n| home_town          = \n| title              = \n| boards             = Young Academy at [[Royal Netherlands Academy of Arts and Sciences]]\n| spouse             = \n| partner            = \n| children           = \n| parents            =\n| relatives          =\n| awards             = Netherlands Organization for Scientific Research award\n| website            = \n| education          = \n| alma_mater         = [[TU Delft]]\n| thesis_title       = \n| thesis_url         = \n| thesis_year        = \n| school_tradition   = \n| doctoral_advisor   = \n| academic_advisors  = \n| influences         = <!--must be referenced from a third party source-->\n| era                = \n| discipline         = Ethycist\n| sub_discipline     = Ethics and Technology <br> Ethics and Nuclear Energy\n| workplaces         = [[TU Delft]], [[Harvard University]]\n| doctoral_students  = <!--only those with WP articles-->\n| notable_students   = <!--only those with WP articles-->\n| main_interests     = \n| notable_works      = Ethics and governance of multinational nuclear waste repositories\n| notable_ideas      = \n| influenced         = <!--must be referenced from a third party source-->\n| signature          = \n| signature_alt      = \n| signature_size     = \n| footnotes          = \n}}\n'''Behnam Taebi''' is a Dutch-Iranian ethicist and academician who is known for his research at the interface of Ethics and Nuclear Energy. He is currently an Associate Professor in ethics of technology at Delft University of Technology,<ref>{{cite web |title=Dr.ir. B. (Behnam) Taebi |url=https://www.tudelft.nl/en/tpm/about-the-faculty/departments/values-technology-and-innovation/people/associate-professors/drir-b-behnam-taebi/ |website=TU Delft |accessdate=27 January 2019 |language=en}}</ref> and Associate with the Kennedy School's [[Belfer Center for Science and International Affairs]] at [[Harvard University]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Behnam Taebi |url=https://www.belfercenter.org/person/behnam-taebi |website=Belfer Center for Science and International Affairs |accessdate=27 January 2019 |language=en}}</ref> In 2016, Taebi has been appointed to the Young Academy at the [[Royal Netherlands Academy of Arts and Sciences]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Newsmakers |url=https://www.belfercenter.org/publication/newsmakers-0 |website=Belfer Center for Science and International Affairs |accessdate=27 January 2019 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Taebi, Dr. ir. B. (Behnam) \u00e2\u20ac |url=https://www.dejongeakademie.nl/nl/leden/leden/14998 |website=www.dejongeakademie.nl |accessdate=27 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nTaebi studied Material Science and Engineering (2006) and received his Ph.D. in Philosophy of Technology (2010) at TU Delft in the Netherlands. He went to Harvard University in the US to perform his post-doctorate research where he established a firm tie with American research institute in ethical technology. His research interests are in energy ethics, nuclear ethics, responsible research and innovation (RRI) and engineering ethics. Taebi has finished a Veni project (2014-2018) and he is currently working on a joint RRI project on understanding controversies in energy technologies (both projects awarded by the Netherlands Organization for Scientific Research).\n\n==Academic career and coverage==\nHis work around the safety and ethical aspects of nuclear energy technology and systems or his contribution in critical nuclear debates have been extensively covered by media outlet in the USA such as [[New York Times]],<ref>{{cite web |last1=Taebi |first1=Behnam |title=Opinion {{!}} The Burden of Nuclear Waste |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/08/30/opinion/30iht-edtaebi.html |website=The New York Times |accessdate=27 January 2019 |date=29 August 2010}}</ref> [[Huffington Post]],<ref>{{cite web |last1=Taebi |first1=Behnam |title=Volkswagen Scandal Reveals Design Flaws: The Need for Value Conscious Design |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/behnam-taebi/volkswagen-scandal-reveal_b_8280708.html?ec_carp=6394260751505444439 |website=Huffington Post |accessdate=27 January 2019 |date=13 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Taebi |first1=Behnam |title=Dutch Court Breaks Political Stalemate Over Climate Action |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/dutch-court-breaks-politi_us_5bb90426e4b0877501042281 |website=Huffington Post |accessdate=27 January 2019 |date=7 July 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Taebi |first1=Behnam |title=The Russian Nuclear Energy Proposal: An Offer You Can't Refuse |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/the-russian-nuclear-energ_us_5bb8fea3e4b0877501032cf0 |website=Huffington Post |accessdate=27 January 2019 |date=5 June 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Taebi |first1=Behnam |title=Why Rejecting Students Based on Nationality Is a Bad Idea for Universities and for the U.S. |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/why-rejecting-students-based-on-nationality-is-a-bad-idea-for-universities-and-for-the-us_us_5bae567de4b022a916cafc60 |website=Huffington Post |accessdate=27 January 2019 |date=13 March 2015}}</ref> [[Newsweek]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Behnam Taebi: Disposing of nuclear waste is a challenge for humanity {{!}} Opinion |url=https://www.newsweek.com/disposing-nuclear-waste-challenge-humanity-behnam-taebi-609468 |website=Newsweek |accessdate=27 January 2019 |language=en |date=15 May 2017}}</ref> Reuters,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Contributor |first1=Guest |title=Multinational repositories can address nuclear waste stockpile |url=http://blogs.reuters.com/great-debate-uk/2013/11/25/multinational-repositories-can-address-nuclear-waste-stockpile/ |website=Reuters Blogs |accessdate=27 January 2019 |date=25 November 2013}}</ref> and academic media such as National Interest <ref>{{cite web |last1=Kathleen Ara\u00fajo |first1=Behnam Taebi |title=Where Should Nuclear Waste be Dumped? |url=https://nationalinterest.org/feature/where-should-nuclear-waste-be-dumped-12961 |website=The National Interest |accessdate=27 January 2019 |language=en |date=26 May 2015}}</ref> and [[Thomson Reuters Foundation]] <ref>{{cite web |author=Thomson Reuters Foundation |title=Innovation to tackle climate change must be socially responsible |url=http://news.trust.org//item/20150420120307-djt7u/?source=jtBlogs |website=news.trust.org |accessdate=27 January 2019}}</ref> and Carnegie Council <ref>{{cite web |title=The Intergenerational and International Justice Dilemmas of Multinational Nuclear Waste Repositories {{!}} Carnegie Council for Ethics in International Affairs |url=https://www.carnegiecouncil.org/publications/ethics_online/0094 |website=www.carnegiecouncil.org |accessdate=27 January 2019}}</ref> and also in the Netherlands media.<ref>{{cite web |last1=NTR |first1=Omroep |title=Podcast - Kernenergie |url=https://www.dekennisvannu.nl/site/media/Podcast---Kernenergie/6074 |website=De Kennis van Nu |accessdate=27 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Kamperman en Taebi gemist? Kijk op npo3.nl |url=https://www.npo3.nl/veelbelovend-3/06-10-2017/WO_NTR_11137379 |website=npo3.nl |accessdate=27 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Science Cafe Enschede -  Behnam Taebi |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0oxbrPAhuS4 |accessdate=27 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Behnam Taebi: \"Kernenergie is kiezen tussen kwaden\" |url=https://downtoearthmagazine.nl/behnam-taebi-kernenergie-kiezen-tussen-kwaden/ |website=Down To Earth Magazine |accessdate=27 January 2019 |language=nl |date=9 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Publication==\nIn addition to scholary articles Taebi published within the ethics and technology,<ref>{{cite web |title=Behnam Taebi - Google Scholar Citations |url=https://scholar.google.nl/citations?user=BKyKDQoAAAAJ&hl=en |website=scholar.google.nl |accessdate=27 January 2019}}</ref> he authored the book 'The Ethics of Nuclear Energy Risk, Justice, and Democracy in the Post-Fukushima Era' published by [[Cambridge University Press]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Ethics nuclear energy risk justice and democracy post fukushima era {{!}} Political philosophy |url=https://www.cambridge.org/au/academic/subjects/philosophy/political-philosophy/ethics-nuclear-energy-risk-justice-and-democracy-post-fukushima-era |website=Cambridge University Press |accessdate=27 January 2019 |language=en}}</ref> later became known as a standard text within the field.\nTaebi is also the author of 'The Morally Desirable Option for Nuclear Power Production (2011)' and the editor of several volumes, including 'The Socio-Technical Challenges of Nuclear Power Production and Waste Management (2015)' <ref>{{cite web |title=Ethics nuclear energy risk justice and democracy post fukushima era {{!}} Political philosophy |url=https://www.cambridge.org/au/academic/subjects/philosophy/political-philosophy/ethics-nuclear-energy-risk-justice-and-democracy-post-fukushima-era#bookPeople |website=Cambridge University Press |accessdate=27 January 2019 |language=en}}</ref> and also a co-author for 'Responsible Innovation in Energy Projects: Values in the Design of Technologies, Institutions and Stakeholder Interactions (2015)'.<ref>{{cite web |title=Responsible Innovation in Energy Projects: Values in the Design of Technologies, Institutions and Stakeholder Interactions |url=https://www.belfercenter.org/node/89219 |website=Belfer Center for Science and International Affairs |accessdate=27 January 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Ethics of technology]]\n*[[Digital ethics]]\n*[[Engineering ethics]]\n*[[Philosophy of technology]]\n\n==External links==\n* [https://ethicsandtechnology.eu/member/taebi/ Personal page]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n[[Category:Dutch ethicists]]\n[[Category:Delft University of Technology faculty]]\n[[Category:Delft University of Technology alumni]]\n[[Category:Dutch scientists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Members of the Royal Netherlands Academy of Arts and Sciences]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Dutch ethicist and academician|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Orphan|date=February 2019}}\n\n{{Infobox academic\n| honorific_prefix   = \n| name               = Behnam Taebi\n| honorific_suffix   = \n| image              = \n| image_size         = \n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| native_name        = \u0628\u0647\u0646\u0627\u0645 \u062a\u0627\u0626\u0628\u06cc\n| native_name_lang   = Persian\n| birth_name         = Behnam Taebi\n| birth_date         = \n| birth_place        = 1977\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| death_cause        = \n| region             = \n| nationality        = Dutch\n| citizenship        = Dutch\n| residence          = [[The Netherlands]]\n| other_names        = \n| occupation         = \n| period             = \n| known_for          = \n| home_town          = \n| title              = \n| boards             = Young Academy at [[Royal Netherlands Academy of Arts and Sciences]]\n| spouse             = \n| partner            = \n| children           = \n| parents            =\n| relatives          =\n| awards             = N